11.name: Trailblaze Power
11.description:
Trailblaze Power will constantly regenerate at a rate of 1 point every 6 minutes to a max of **240** points. You may exchange Stellar Jade for Trailblaze Power.
When Trailblaze Power has been fully regenerated or exceeds the maximum accumulation amount, it will no longer regenerate. At the same time, Reserved Trailblaze Power will begin to regenerate over time.

12.name: Reserved Trailblaze Power
12.description:
When Trailblaze Power reaches or exceeds the max limit, Reserved Trailblaze Power will begin to regenerate over time. Reserved Trailblaze Power recovers 1 point every **18** minutes for a max of **2400** points.
Reserved Trailblaze Power can withdraw an equivalent amount of Trailblaze Power for a max of **240** points each time.

250201.name: Malfunctioning Chip
250201.description: Attacking a debuffed enemy deals Additional DMG to them.

250202.name: Defective Suppression Chip
250202.description: When an enemy is defeated, all other enemies' actions are greatly delayed.

250203.name: Emergency Reboot Chip
250203.description: When struck by a killing blow, instead of being knocked down, immediately restores HP and gains an additional turn. This effect can only trigger 1 time per battle.

250204.name: Trotter Patch Chip
250204.description: When equipped by a Trotter, greatly Enhances it.

250205.name: Morale Activation Chip
250205.description: After an ally launches an attack, receive Morale. Morale increases all ally stats.

250207.name: Performance Allocation Chip
250207.description: When an enemy is defeated, regenerates 1 Energy for all other allies, 1 time per turn.

250208.name: Efficiency Optimization Chip
250208.description: After entering combat, reduces the Energy required for Ultimate by 1. Energy can be reduced by up to 2 points max.

250209.name: High Load-Low Speed Chip
250209.description: Greatly increases ATK and greatly reduces SPD.

250210.name: Sudden Evasion Chip
250210.description: During the first 2 turns of battle, greatly reduces DMG received.

250211.name: Safe Mode Chip
250211.description: Greatly reduces ATK and greatly increases Max HP.

250212.name: Threshold Disruption Chip
250212.description: When attacking enemy targets with HP percentage greater than a certain amount, greatly increases the DMG dealt by the attack.

250213.name: Freeze Loophole Chip
250213.description: Upon entering battle, causes all enemies to Freeze.

250214.name: Shield System Chip
250214.description: Greatly increases chance to be attacked. Upon entering battle, obtains a Shield.

250215.name: Backstage Enhancement Chip
250215.description: The wearer's ATK is greatly increased when it is not currently their turn.

250216.name: Sudden Interjection Chip
250216.description: After the first action, immediately gains an additional turn.

250217.name: Wind Shear Loophole Chip
250217.description: After attacking, there is a chance of inflicting Wind Shear on the target.

250218.name: Matrix Iteration Chip
250218.description: After using their Ultimate, the wearer restores a massive amount of HP.

250219.name: Attack Interception Chip
250219.description: At the end of the wearer's action, they gain a Barrier that nullifies all DMG received except DoTs.

250220.name: Auto-Repair Chip
250220.description: Restores a minor amount of HP after the wearer takes action. Each time this is triggered, the HP restored increases.

250221.name: Data Retrieval Chip
250221.description: After defeating an enemy, the wearer restores a massive amount of HP.

250222.name: Parallel Enhancement Chip
250222.description: After using an attack, increase DMG received by the wearer and the attacked enemies.

250223.name: Saturated Activation Chip
250223.description: When the wearer's first turn begins, immediately regenerates a certain amount of Energy.

250224.name: Quick Command Chip
250224.description: Consume all Skill Points after using a Basic ATK or Skill to take an extra action. This cannot be triggered consecutively.

250225.name: Shieldbreaker Chip
250225.description: When attacking Shielded enemy targets, greatly increases the DMG dealt by the attack.

250226.name: Functional Overdraft Chip
250226.description: After attacking the enemy target, the wearer consumes their own HP and greatly Advances their action Forward.

250227.name: Energy Recycling Chip
250227.description: After using their Ultimate to defeat enemy targets, the wearer regenerates their Energy to max.

250228.name: Computation Lock Chip
250228.description: Greatly increases ATK, but disables Ultimate.

250229.name: Cleansing Chip
250229.description: Dispels one buff on the target when attacking. If the buff is successfully dispelled, increase the DMG of this attack.

250230.name: Firewall Chip
250230.description: Increases Max HP and greatly increases the chance of enemies attacking the wearer.

250231.name: Negative Load Algorithm Chip
250231.description: Increases DMG dealt based on the number of debuffs on the wearer.

250232.name: Deep Clean Chip
250232.description: At the end of the turn, removes all debuffs from the wearer, and removes 1 debuff from each of the other allies.

250320.name: Aether Spirit Upgrade Data

408619.description: Upon use, increases all allies' ATK by **40%** for the next battle. When entering battle, a random character will have a **100%** base chance to become afflicted with Outrage, lasting for 2 turns.

408620.name: Dreamville Special
408620.description: Upon use, one of the following effects will be randomly applied to all allies in the next battle: Clockie's Whirlwind Fruit Tea — ATK increases by **36%**. Brother Hanu's Boba Tea — CRIT Rate increases by **18%**. Mr. Soda's Orange-Peel Latte — CRIT DMG increases by **36%**.

408621.name: Sweet Dreams Holographic Ticket
408621.description: Upon use, one of the following effects will be randomly applied to all allies in the next battle: Mirror Princess Edition — DEF increases by **36%**. Miss Note Edition — Max HP increases by **30%**.

408622.name: Odd Gummy Candy
408622.description: Upon use, one of the following effects will be randomly applied to all allies in the next battle: Hamster Ball Knight Flavor — SPD increases by **20%**. Boss Stone Flavor — SPD decreases by 5%.

408623.name: Origami Family Bucket
408623.description: Upon use, one of the following effects will be randomly applied to all allies: Serious Professor Owl — DMG dealt increases by **36%**. Mischievous Origami Bird — DMG taken increases by **10%**.

408624.name: Polychromatic Sourness
408624.description: When used, increase all allies' ATK by **24%**, CRIT DMG by **20%**, and decrease their Ultimate DMG dealt by **12%** in the next battle.

408625.name: Unsolvable Cube
408625.description: When used, after allies attack for the first time in the next battle, the attacked enemy target will heal for an amount equal to the HP it lost in this attack. For every 1% of HP the enemy target heals in this way, characters receive a Shield that can block DMG that is equal to 1% of the character's Max HP, up to **100%** of their Max HP, lasting for 2 turns.

408626.name: Broken String's Roar
408626.description: When used, the ally character with the highest current ATK deals **35%** more DMG in the next battle, and their likelihood of being attacked by enemy targets is increased greatly.

408627.name: Soundless Satisfaction
408627.description: When used, all allies' Basic ATK DMG increases by **45%** and Skill DMG decreases by **12%** in the next battle.

408628.name: Sparkle's Limited Edition Collectible Figure
408628.description: Upon use, increases all allies' CRIT DMG by **36%** for the next battle.

408629.name: Goldsteels
408629.description: Upon use, immediately heals a target ally for **45%** of their Max HP.

408630.name: Goldsteels
408630.description: Upon use, immediately heals a target ally for **45%** of their Max HP.

408801.name: Dreamy Cone (Three Flavors)
408801.description: Upon use, increases all allies' ATK by **60%** for the next battle. There is a small chance to select the wrong target when using abilities against enemy targets.

408802.name: All or Nothing
408802.description: Upon use, your next draw for the Lucky Wheel in Penacony guarantees you a "special prize."
